  "body": "### Description\nP2P Messages of >16 KB are fragmented by the TLS protocol into TLS records. The RLPx decoder implementation doesn't allow them to be reconstructed, it just takes the first TLS record as the whole message, so effectively truncates the message, which leads to RLP decoding errors and therefore BREACH_OF_PROTOCOL.\n\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\n1. Enable TLS on a network of 2+ nodes\n2. Create a large RLPx message (> 16KB) e.g. by sending 1000 transactions concurrently so they are put into a single block\n3. Peers that receive the large message will yield a BREACH_OF_PROTOCOL at the DEBUG log level and will disconnect.\n\n**Expected behavior:** [What you expect to happen]\nMessages of varying sizes should be handled the same way as when TLS is disabled.\n\n**Actual behavior:** [What actually happens]\nLarge messages are truncated and peers are disconnected due to BREACH_OF_PROTOCOL.\n\n**Frequency:** [What percentage of the time does it occur?]\nOnly when a large message is encountered.",
